obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4800)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4800&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Factoring Regulation`
  line `Act, 2011.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 2nd April, 2012 (Ss. 19, 20, 21, 32), vide notification No. S.O. 711(E), dated 2nd April, 2012, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line
  line `1st February, 2012 (expect ss. 19, 20, 21 and 32), vide notification No. S.O. 1399(E), dated 21st June, 2012, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4801)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4801&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) assignment means ^1[`
  line `transfer by agreement to a factor of an undivided interest, in whole or`
  line `in part, in the receivables of an assignor due from a debtor and includes such transfer where either the`
  line `assignor or the debtor is situated or established outside India].`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this clause, undivided interest of any assignor in any`
  line `receivable shall not include creation of rights in receivables as security for loans and advances or`
  line `other obligations by a bank or a financial institution;`
  line
  line `(b) assignee means a factor in whose favour the receivable is transferred;`
  line
  line `(c) assignor means any person who is the owner of any receivable;`
  line
  line `(d) bank means,`
  line
  line `(i) a banking company;`
  line
  line `(ii) a corresponding new bank;`
  line
  line `(iii) the State Bank of India;`
  line
  line `(iv) a subsidiary bank;`
  line
  line `(v) such other bank which the Central Government may by notification specify for the purposes`
  line `of this Act on the recommendations of the Reserve Bank; or`
  line
  line `(vi) a Multi-State Co-operative Society registered under the Multi-State Co-operative Societies`
  line `Act, 2002 (39 of 2002) and licensed to undertake business of banking by the Reserve Bank under`
  line `the provisions of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(e) banking company shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(f) business enterprise means any enterprise or medium enterprise, micro enterprise or small`
  line `enterprise as defined in clauses (e), (g), (h) and (m) of section 2 of the Micro, Small and Medium`
  line `Enterprises Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006), respectively engaged in any business activity;`
  line
  line `(g) corresponding new bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (da) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(h) debtor' means any person liable to the assignor, whether under a contract or otherwise, to`
  line `pay any receivable or discharge any obligation in respect of the receivable whether existing, accruing,`
  line `future, conditional or contingent;`
  line
  line `(i) factor means a non-banking financial company as defined in clause (f) of section 45-I of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) which has been granted a certificate of registration`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 or anybody corporate established under an Act of Parliament or any`
  line `State Legislature or any Bank or any company registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `engaged in the factoring business;`
  line
  line `(j) factoring business means the business of ^2[`
  line `acquisition by way of assignment of receivables`
  line `of assignor for a consideration for the purpose of collection of such receivables or for financing,`
  line `whether by way of making loans or advances or otherwise, against such assignment, but]does not`
  line include
  line
  line `(i) credit facilities provided by a bank ^3[ or a non-banking financial company] in its ordinary course of business against security of`
  line receivables;
  line
  line `(ii) any activity as commission agent or otherwise for sale of agricultural produce or goods of`
  line `any kind whatsoever or any activity relating to the production, storage, supply, distribution,`
  line `acquisition or control of such produce or goods or provision of any services.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this clause`
  line
  line `(i) the expression agricultural produce shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause`
  line `(a) of section 2 of the Agricultural Produce (Grading and Marking) Act, 1937 (1 of 1937); and`
  line
  line `(ii) the expressions goods and commission agent shall have the meanings assigned to`
  line `them respectively under clause (d) and Explanation (ii) of clause (i) of section 2 of the Forward`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(k) financial contract means any spot, forward, future, option or swap transaction involving`
  line `interest rates, commodities, currencies, shares, bonds, debentures or any other financial instrument,`
  line `any repurchase of securities and lending transaction or any other similar transaction or combination of`
  line `such transactions entered into in the financial markets;`
  line
  line `(l) netting agreement means any agreement among the system participants for the purpose of`
  line `determination by the system provider of the amount of money or securities due or payable or`
  line `deliverable as a result of setting off or adjusting the payment obligations or delivery obligations`
  line `among the system participants, including the claims and obligations arising out of the termination by`
  line `the system provider, on the insolvency or dissolution or winding up of any system participant or such`
  line `circumstances as the system provider, may specify in its rules or regulations or bye-laws (by whatever`
  line `name called), of the transactions admitted for settlement at a future date so that only a net claim be`
  line `demanded or a net obligation be owned;`
  line
  line `(m) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(n) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) property means,`
  line
  line `(i) the immovable property;`
  line
  line `(ii) the movable property;`
  line
  line `(iii) any debt or any right to receive payment of money, whether secured or unsecured;`
  line
  line `(iv) the receivables;`
  line
  line `(v) the intangible assets, being know-how, patent, copyright, design, trade mark, licence, franchise or any other business or commercial right of similar nature;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(p) receivables means the money owed by a debtor and not yet paid to the assignor for goods`
  line `or services and includes payment of any sum, by whatever name called, required to be paid for the`
  line `toll or for the use of any infrastructure facility or services;`
  line
  line `(pa) regulations means regulations made by the Reserve Bank under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(q) Reserve Bank, means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(r) State Bank of India means the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(s) Subsidiary Bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (k) of section 2 of the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `^5[(sa) Trade Receivables Discounting System means a payment system authorised by the`
  line `Reserve Bank under section 7 of the Payment and Settlement Systems Act, 2007 (51 of 2007) for the`
  line `purpose of facilitating financing of trade receivables;]`
  line
  line `(t) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), the Credit Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005), or the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act, 21 of 2021, s. 2, for the certain words (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 21 of 2021, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by Act 21 of 2021, s. 2, for clause (p) (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4802)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registration of factors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4802&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No factor shall commence or carry on the factoring business unless it`
  line `obtains a certificate of registration from the Reserve Bank to commence or carry on the factoring business`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every factor shall make an application for registration to the Reserve Bank in such form and`
  line `manner as it may specify:`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(3) Every applicant for grant of a certificate of a registration as a factor shall comply, for the purpose`
  line `of registration, with all the requirements to be fulfilled by an applicant for grant of certificate of`
  line `registration as non-banking financial company under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) and`
  line `all the provisions of that Act, so far as they relate to the registration of non-banking financial companies,`
  line `shall (except those provided for under this Act) mutatis mutandis apply.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The Reserve Bank may grant the certificate of registration in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.]`
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, every factor including factors not subject to requirement of`
  line `registration under section 5, shall be governed by the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), the rules and regulations made thereunder and the directions or guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank, from`
  line `time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.The proviso and Explanation omitted by Act 21 of 2021, s. 3 (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4803)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Provisions of non-banking financial companies apply to factor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4803&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `All provisions of Chapter`
  line `IIIB of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) relating to non-banking financial companies`
  line `which have been granted a certificate of registration under sub-section (5) of section 45-IA of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 shall (except those specifically provided for under this Act) mutatis mutandis`
  line `apply to a factor which has been granted a certificate of registration under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4804)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Requirement for registration as a factor not to apply to bank or Statutory corporation or Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4804&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in section 3 shall apply to a bank or any corporation`
  line `established under an Act of Parliament or State Legislature, or a Government Company as defined under`
  line `section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4805)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of Reserve Bank to give directions and to collect information from factors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4805&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Reserve Bank may, at any time by general or special order, direct that every factor shall furnish to it, in`
  line `such form, at such intervals and within such time, such statements, information or particulars relating to`
  line `factoring business undertaken by the factor, as may be specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, if it considers necessary in the interest of business enterprises availing`
  line `factoring services or in the interest of factors or interest of other stake holders give directions to the`
  line `factors either generally or to any factor in particular or group of factors in respect of any matters relating`
  line `to or connected with the factoring business undertaken by such factors.`
  line
  line `(3) If any factor fails to comply with any direction given by the Reserve Bank under sub-section (2),`
  line `the Reserve Bank may prohibit such factor from undertaking the factoring business:`
  line
  line `Provided that before prohibiting any factor from undertaking the factoring business, the factor shall`
  line `be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4806)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Assignment of receivables.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4806&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assignor may, by an agreement in writing, assign any`
  line `receivable due and payable to him by any debtor, to any factor, being the assignee, for a consideration as`
  line `may be agreed between the assignor and the assignee and the assignor shall at the time of such`
  line `assignment, disclose to the assignee any defences and right of set off that may be available to the debtor:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the debtor liable to pay the receivable or the business of factor is situated or`
  line `established outside India, any assignment of receivable shall be subject to the provisions of the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999).`
  line
  line `(2) On execution of agreement in writing for assignment of receivables, all the rights, remedies and`
  line `any security interest created over any property exclusively to secure the due payment of receivable shall`
  line `vest in the assignee and the assignee shall have an absolute right to recover such receivable and exercise`
  line `all the rights and remedies of the assignor whether by way of damages or otherwise, or whether notice of`
  line `assignment as provided in section 8 is given or not.`
  line
  line `(3) Any assignment of receivables which constitute security for repayment of any loan advanced by`
  line `any Bank or other creditor and if the assignor has given notice of such encumbrance to the assignee, then`
  line `on accepting assignment of such receivable, the assignee shall pay the consideration for such assignment`
  line `to the Bank or the creditor, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4807)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Notice to debtor and discharge of obligation of such debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4807&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Any assignee of a receivable`
  line `shall not be entitled to demand payment of the receivable from the debtor in respect of such receivables`
  line `unless notice of such assignment is given to the debtor by the assignor or the assignee along with express`
  line `authority in its favors granted by the assignor.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4808)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Discharge of liability of debtor on payment to assignee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4808&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where a notice of assignment of`
  line `receivable is given by the assignor or the assignee, as the case may be, under section 8 the debtor on`
  line `receipt of such notice, shall make payment to the assignee and payment made to such assignee in discharge of any obligation in relation to the receivables specified in the notice shall fully discharge the`
  line `debtor making the payment, from corresponding liability in respect of such payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4809)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Payment made by debtor to assignor to be held in trust for benefit of assignee in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4809&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where no notice of assignment of receivables is given by the assignor or under his authority by`
  line `the assignee, any payment made by the debtor in respect of such receivables to the assignor shall be held`
  line `in trust for the benefit of the assignee which shall be forthwith be paid over to such assignee, as the case`
  line `may be, or its agent duly authorised in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4810)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Rights and obligations of parties to contract for assignment of receivables.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4810&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line Without
  line `prejudice to the provisions contained in any other law for the time being in force, the debtor shall have the`
  line `right to notice of assignment under section 8 before any demand is made on it by the assignee and until`
  line `notice is served on the debtor, the debtor shall be entitled to make payments to the assignor in respect of`
  line `assigned receivables in accordance with the original contract and such payment shall fully discharge the`
  line `debtor from corresponding liability under the original contract.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall affect the rights of debtor to make payment to the assignee under section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4811)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Liability of debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4811&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where a notice of assignment as referred to in section 8 is served, the`
  line `debtor shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) intimate the assignee the details of the deposits or advance or payment on account made to`
  line `the assignor before the receipt of notice of assignment and also provide any other information to the`
  line `assignee relating to the receivable as and when called upon by the assignee to do so;`
  line
  line `(b) not be entitled to a valid discharge of his liability in respect of assigned receivables, unless he`
  line `makes the payment due on an assigned receivables to the assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4812)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Assignor to be trustee of assignee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4812&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, where a debtor makes any payment to an assignor which represents`
  line `payment due on an assigned receivable, such payment shall be deemed to be for the benefit of the`
  line `assignee, and the assignor shall be deemed to have received the amount of such payment as a trustee of`
  line `the assignee and the assignor shall make payment of such amount to the assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4813)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Liability of debtor in case of an assignor being mircro or small enterprises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4813&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `assignor of receivables is a micro or small enterprise, the liability of the debtor to make payment due on`
  line `assigned receivables shall be subject to the provisions contained in sections 15 to 17 of the Micro, Small`
  line `and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006) with regards to the delayed payments of`
  line `the receivables.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of delay in payment on the part of the debtor to pay the receivable of any micro or`
  line `small enterprise, the assignee shall be entitled to receive interest for the delayed period and shall take`
  line `steps under the provisions of the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006`
  line `(27 of 2006) for the purpose of the recovery of the interest and shall pay such interest to the micro or`
  line `small enterprise.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4814)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Principle of debtor protection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4814&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, any assignment of`
  line `the receivable shall not, without the express consent of the debtor in writing, affect the rights and`
  line `obligations of the debtor (including the terms and conditions of the contract).`
  line
  line `(2) Consequent upon the assignment of receivables, the payment instruction under the contract`
  line `entered into between assignor and debtor may modify the name of person, address or account to which the`
  line `debtor is required to make payment, but such instructions shall not modify:—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of debt specified in the original contract; or`
  line
  line `(b) the place specified in the original contract at which payment is to be made or in case no such`
  line `place is mentioned in the contract, the place of payment to a place other than where the debtor is`
  line `situated; or`
  line
  line `(c) the date on which payment is to be made or other terms of the original contract relating to`
  line payment.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4815)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Defences and right of set off of debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4815&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `In a claim by the assignee against the debtor for`
  line `payment of the assigned receivable, the debtor may raise against the assignee,—`
  line
  line `(a) all defences and right of set off arising from the original contract, entered into between the`
  line `assignor and debtor or any other contract that was part of the same transaction, of which the debtor`
  line `could avail himself as if the assignment had not been made and such claim were made by the assignor`
  line `instead of assignee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the assignee shall, unless otherwise agreed between the parties, be entitled to`
  line `recover from the assignor, any loss suffered by it as a result of any such defences and right of set off`
  line `being exercised by the debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) any other right of set off if it was available to the debtor at the time notice, under section 8, of`
  line `the assignment was received by the debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4816)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Modification of original contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4816&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any agreement made before service of notice, under`
  line `section 8, of the assignment of a receivable between the assignor and the debtor that affects the assignee's`
  line `rights in respect of that receivable shall be effective as against the assignee, and the assignee shall acquire`
  line `rights in the assigned receivables, as modified by such agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Any agreement made, after notice of the assignment between the assignor and the debtor that`
  line `affects the assignee's rights, shall be ineffective as against the assignee unless,—`
  line
  line `(a) the assignee consents to it; or`
  line
  line `(b) the receivable is not fully earned by performance and either the modification is provided for in`
  line `the original contract or, in the context of the original contract, a reasonable assignee would consent to`
  line `the modification.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall affect any right of the assignor or the assignee`
  line `arising from breach of an agreement between them.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4817)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Breach of contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4817&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If the assignor commits any breach of the original contract with the debtor,`
  line `such breach shall not entitle the debtor to recover from the assignee any sum paid by the debtor to the`
  line `assignor or the assignee pursuant to the factoring transactions:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the rights of the debtor to claim from the`
  line `assignor any loss or damages caused to him by reason of breach of the original contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4818)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Registration of certain assignments of receivables transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4818&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)Every factor shall`
  line `register the particulars of every transaction of assignment of receivables in his favour with the Central`
  line `Registry set-up under section 20 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and`
  line `Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), within such time from the date of such`
  line `assignment, in such manner and subject to payment of such fee, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purpose of filing of particulars of every transaction of assignment of`
  line `receivables with the Central Registry, the receivables may be described specifically or generally with`
  line `reference to the debtor, or the period to which they relate or by any other general description by which`
  line `such receivables can be identified.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Where any trade receivables are financed through a Trade Receivables Discounting System,`
  line `the particulars specified in sub-section (1) and sub-section (3) shall be filed with the Central Registry on`
  line `behalf of the factor by the Trade Receivables Discounting System concerned, in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, a record called the Central Register shall be kept at the head office of`
  line `the Central Registry for entering the particulars of the transactions relating to assignment of receivables in`
  line `favour of a factor.`
  line
  line `(3) On realisation of the assigned receivables or settlement of the claim against the debtors, the factor`
  line `shall file satisfaction of the assignment of receivables in its favour, in such manner and subject to`
  line `payment of such fees as may be prescribed in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions for registration of transactions contained in the Securitisation and Reconstruction`
  line `of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002) and the rules made`
  line `thereunder shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the record of assignment of receivables in favour of a factor`
  line `in the Central Register with the Central Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2021, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2.Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4819)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4819&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The particulars of transactions of assignment of receivables entered in`
  line `the Central Register of such transactions under section 19 shall be open during business hours for`
  line `inspection by any person on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Register referred to in sub-section (2) of section 19 maintained in electronic form,`
  line `shall also be open during the business hours or such extended hours as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Registry for inspection by any person through electronic media on payment of such fee as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions for maintenance of Central Register and public inspection thereof contained in the`
  line `Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002`
  line `(54 of 2002) and the rules made thereunder shall, mutatis mutandis, apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4820)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 21 and 22 (w.e.f. 22-01-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4820&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Penalties.-- If a default is made in filing under section 19, the particulars of any transaction of`
  line `assignment of receivables and realisation of receivables by a factor, such company and every officer of`
  line `the company who is in default shall be liable to penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees and in the`
  line `case of a continuing offence, with an additional penalty which may extend to ten thousand rupees for`
  line `every day during which the default continues, to be imposed by the Reserve Bank in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of subsections (2) to (4) of section 22.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4821)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Penalties for non-compliance of direction of Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 21 and 22 (w.e.f. 22-01-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4821&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Penalties for non-compliance of direction by Reserve Bank.—(1) If any factor fails to comply`
  line `with any direction issued by the Reserve Bank under section 6, the Reserve Bank may impose a penalty`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing offence, with an additional fine`
  line `which may extend to ten thousand rupees for every day during which the default continues.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of adjudging the penalty under sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank shall serve`
  line `notice on the factor requiring it to show cause why the amount specified in the notice should not be`
  line `imposed and a reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such factor.`
  line
  line `(3) Any penalty imposed by the Reserve Bank under this section shall be payable within a period of`
  line `fourteen days from the date on which notice issued by the Reserve Bank demanding payment of the sum`
  line `is served on the factor and in the event of failure of the factor to pay the sum within such period, may be`
  line `levied on a direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction in the area where the registered`
  line `office of the factor is situated; or, in the case of a factor incorporated outside India, where its principal`
  line `place of business in India is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be made except on an application made to the court by the`
  line `Reserve Bank or any officer authorised by Reserve Bank in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The court which makes a direction under sub-section (3) shall issue a certificate specifying the`
  line `sum payable by the factor and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it were`
  line `a decree made by the court in a civil suit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4822)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4822&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If any person contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rules made thereunder, for which no specific penalty has been provided`
  line `for, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4823)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4823&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act except upon a complaint in writing made by an officer of the Reserve Bank, generally or`
  line `specially authorised in writing in this behalf by the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or`
  line `a court superior thereto shall try any such offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4824)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Offences by factors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4824&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a factor, every`
  line `person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the factor, for`
  line `the conduct of the business of the factor, as well as the factor, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he has exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a factor and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the factor, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, a "director", in relation to a factor means any officer`
  line `entrusted with the management of the whole or substantially the affairs of the factor.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4825)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Provisions of this Act to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4825&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect,`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4826)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4826&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder`
  line `shall be in addition to and not in derogation of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881), the`
  line `Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Securitisation and`
  line `Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), the`
  line `Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4827)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4827&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No assignee of any receivable shall be entitled to take any measures for recovery of`
  line `any assigned receivable, through any court or Tribunal unless his claim in respect of the receivable is`
  line `made within the period of limitation specified under the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4828)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Confidentiality of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4828&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, or unless required to`
  line `do so by an order passed by any Court or Tribunal or any other statutory authority under any provision of`
  line `law for the time being in force or for the purpose of recovery of the receivable, a factor shall maintain`
  line `confidentiality and shall not disclose to any person information obtained by it from, any assignor, its`
  line `present and future customers, its commercial and business activities and the terms of sale between the`
  line `assignor and any debtor and other detail about the assignor.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4829)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4829&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the public interest, direct`
  line `that any of the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) shall not apply to such class or classes of banks or a company or a factor; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to the such class or classes of banks or a company or a factor with such exceptions,`
  line `modifications and adaptations as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification or both the Houses agree that the notification shall not be issued or, the notification shall have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4830)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Provisions of this Act not to apply or affect in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4830&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act`
  line `shall not apply to any assignment of receivables arising under or from the following transactions,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) any merger, acquisition or amalgamation of business activities or sale or change in the`
  line `ownership or legal status of the business;`
  line
  line `(b) transactions on any stock exchange or commodities exchange regulated by the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India constituted under the provisions of the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992(15 of 1992) or by the Forward Markets Commission under the Forward Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952), respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) financial contracts governed by netting agreements, except a receivable owed on the`
  line `termination of all outstanding transactions;`
  line
  line `(d) foreign exchange transactions except receivables in any foreign currency;`
  line
  line `(e) inter-bank payment systems, inter-bank payment agreements or clearance and settlement`
  line `systems relating to securities or other financial assets or instruments;`
  line
  line `(f) bank deposits;`
  line
  line `(g) a letter of credit or independent guarantee;`
  line
  line `(h) rights and obligations of any person under the law governing negotiable instruments,`
  line `negotiable warehouse receipts under the Warehousing (Development and Regulation) Act, 2007`
  line `(37 of 2007) or to instruments which are for the time being, by law or custom negotiable or any`
  line `mercantile document of title to goods;`
  line
  line `(i) sale of goods or services for any personal, family or household use;`
  line
  line `(j) any assignment of loan receivables by a bank or non-banking financial company to another`
  line `bank or non-banking financial company;`
  line
  line `(k) securitisation transactions (including assignment of receivables to special purpose vehicles or`
  line `trusts that issue securities against such receivables, bought from a single debtor or single group of`
  line `debtors).`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Act shall affect the rights and obligations of a consumer, manufacturer,`
  line `trader or service provider under the provisions of the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (57392)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=57392&sectionno=31A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[31A. Power to make regulations.--(1) The Reserve Bank may, by notification, make regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of granting certificate of registration under sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of filling of particulars of transactions with the Central Registry on behalf of`
  line `factors under sub-section (1A) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made by the Reserve Bank, be forwarded to`
  line `the Central Government and ^2`
  line `[that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation, or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall,]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2023, s. 3 and the third Schedule, for "that Central Government" (w.e.f. 17-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4831)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 21 of 2021, s. 6, for “the form and manner” (w.e.f. 23-8-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4831&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank, by notification and in the Electronic Gazette as defined in clause (5)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) ^1[the time within which, the form and manner] in which the transactions of assignment of receivables in favour of a`
  line `factor shall be filed and the fee for filing such transaction under sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which the satisfaction of assignment of receivable or settlement of the`
  line `claim shall be registered and the fee for filing such transactions under sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) fee for inspecting the Central Register under section 20; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed, in respect of which provision is`
  line `to be made or may be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4832)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4832&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4833)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4833&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4834)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Amendments to certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606&sectionId=4834&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00006_201212_1517807327606
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The enactments specified in the Schedule shall be`
  line `amended in the manner specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
